This chart is a version of one from the in-class exercises from week 5, but replaces IMDB votes with worldwide gross as a measure of movie popularity
on the x-axis. Outliers in terms of worldwide gross were removed from the data to better show the spread of the rest of the data.The IMDB rating is
still encoded with position on the y-axis. Movie genre is encoded with color. The problem with the initial graph was that there were too many genre
categories, making it difficult to distinguish between them. This graphic groups sub-genres into 5 major categories to make a color encoding more
appropriate.

A single drop-down menu was added to allow the viewer to separate out points by genre. This interaction is an improvement upon the original improvement
to the graphic, which faceted the chart by genre into multiple charts. This update both maintains the original boundaries of the chart and makes viewing
more categories more feasible. In addition, the tooltip interaction, while not necessary, does allow the user to hover over points and read the movie title.
The tooltip is conditional on which genre is selected as to not cause confusion or clutter.
